==German==

===Etymology===
Possibly from the [[w:Polabian language|Old Polabian]] stem ''berl-''/''birl-'' ([[swamp]]) + suffix ''-in''. The place is first mentioned by this name in the late 12th century (as ''Berlyn''). According to (incorrect) [[folk etymology]], the name is derived from the ''[[Bär]]'' ([[bear]]) that is the symbol of the city.

===Pronunciation===
* (''Standard New High German'') {{IPA|[bɛɐˈliːn]}}, {{IPA|[bɛʁˈliːn]}},
* (''Berlinisch'') {{IPA|[baliːn]}}, {{IPA|[baliːən]}}
* {{Audio|De-Berlin-pronunciation.ogg|Berlin}}

